0f3d4548-63d5-4984-b109-95d22ff4ff9a	2025-01-12 05:12:31.955338+02	2025-01-12 05:21:48.806775+02	post/fff28889b38b4d6696a9482077f884ef.jpg	Empowering Growth Through B-BBEE Consulting and Training	We are dedicated to empowering businesses to thrive in an evolving economic landscape. With our deep expertise and a results-driven approach	empowering-growth-through-b-bbee-consulting-and-training-1	<p>In South Africa, Broad-Based Black Economic Empowerment (B-BBEE) serves as a cornerstone for fostering inclusivity, growth, and economic transformation. This framework is not just about compliance but is a powerful tool for creating opportunities and addressing historical inequalities. At GoldOurs, we recognize the transformative power of B-BBEE and offer expert consulting and training to help businesses, both large and small, unlock their potential while making a positive societal impact.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Why B-BBEE Matters?</strong></p>\r\n<p>B-BBEE ensures that companies contribute to the economic empowerment of previously disadvantaged individuals. It enhances business competitiveness, improves access to government contracts, and boosts market confidence. For small businesses, adhering to B-BBEE standards can open doors to new partnerships and funding opportunities, setting the stage for sustainable growth.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Our Expertise in B-BBEE</strong></p>\r\n<p>GoldOurs boasts a team of seven seasoned experts with qualifications in Industrial Psychology, Economics, Business Leadership, and more. Affiliated with esteemed organizations such as COMENSA, SAICA, and IODSA, our consultants bring over 20 years of average executive experience across private, public, and academic sectors.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What We Offer?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Our B-BBEE consulting and training services are tailored to meet your business's unique needs. Whether you're navigating complex compliance processes or seeking to maximize your scorecard, we provide actionable strategies to help you succeed. We specialize in:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Developing and implementing B-BBEE strategies.</li>\r\n<li>Training your team to understand and embrace the framework.</li>\r\n<li>Offering guidance on leveraging B-BBEE for market advantage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong>The GoldOurs Commitment</strong></h3>\r\n<p>We are dedicated to empowering businesses to thrive in an evolving economic landscape. With our deep expertise and a results-driven approach, we ensure your journey toward B-BBEE compliance is seamless and impactful. Let us be your partner in driving transformation and achieving long-term success.</p>\r\n<p>Invest in your business's future today with GoldOurs' B-BBEE Consulting and Training services&mdash;because growth and inclusivity go hand in hand.</p>	1	0ebaf7ac-d58d-4899-b87e-5f9d6ea0e724
d74bbed7-5cec-4f88-ba8b-d302aeeba0e9	2025-01-12 05:15:54.605832+02	2025-01-12 05:23:35.292743+02	post/d8ead9c92a5d4292accb26e6df3763c6.jpg	Streamlining Success with Systems, Reviews, and Assurance	In today’s fast-paced and highly competitive business environment, organizations must continuously evaluate their systems and processes to remain effective and compliant.	streamlining-success-with-systems-reviews-and-assurance	<p>In today&rsquo;s fast-paced and highly competitive business environment, organizations must continuously evaluate their systems and processes to remain effective and compliant. At GoldOurs, our Systems, Reviews, and Assurance services empower businesses to optimize operations, mitigate risks, and ensure accountability. By focusing on both the public and private sectors, we deliver tailored solutions that drive sustainable growth and excellence.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Why Systems, Reviews, and Assurance Matter?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Effective systems and regular reviews are critical to identifying inefficiencies, ensuring regulatory compliance, and safeguarding assets. Assurance, on the other hand, provides businesses with confidence that their internal controls and governance frameworks meet the highest standards. This is especially vital in industries where financial accuracy and operational reliability directly influence trust and performance.</p>\r\n<p><strong>GoldOurs&rsquo; Expertise?</strong></p>\r\n<p>With a team of eight seasoned experts, GoldOurs combines technical proficiency with industry-leading insights. Our team includes Certified Internal Auditors (CIA), Chartered Accountants (CA(SA)), and specialists with advanced qualifications in accounting and auditing. Affiliated with professional organizations such as SAICA, CIMA, IIA SA, and ACFE, our experts bring over 20 years of average executive experience, spanning both the private and public sectors.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What We Offer?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Our Systems, Reviews, and Assurance services focus on delivering holistic and actionable solutions. Here's how we help businesses excel:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Systems Design and Optimization</strong>: We evaluate and refine your operational systems for efficiency and scalability.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Internal and External Reviews</strong>: Our reviews uncover areas of improvement, helping you strengthen internal controls and governance.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Compliance Assurance</strong>: We provide expert guidance to ensure your business aligns with financial, operational, and regulatory standards.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Fraud Prevention and Risk Management</strong>: By identifying vulnerabilities, we help safeguard your organization from potential risks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Why Choose GoldOurs?</strong></p>\r\n<p>GoldOurs stands out by offering a comprehensive approach to assurance and system reviews. Our team has accumulated over 12 years of public sector expertise, 15 years in the private sector, and a rich understanding of the academic field. This allows us to provide solutions that are both innovative and prac</p>\r\n<p>Whether your organization is undergoing rapid growth, restructuring, or preparing for audits, we are your trusted partner in ensuring that every process is streamlined, secure, and successful.</p>\r\n<p><strong>A Partnership for Growth</strong></p>\r\n<p>By investing in Systems, Reviews, and Assurance, you not only enhance operational efficiency but also build a resilient foundation for future growth. GoldOurs is here to support your journey with unmatched expertise and a commitment to excellence.</p>\r\n<p>Empower your business with GoldOurs. Let&rsquo;s create a system that works for you, delivers assurance, and drives results. Reach out to us today for a consultation!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>	1	62e375f0-94b7-4d43-b3cb-aca1a2957048
20b2ceac-82a6-4e59-8e8d-dd89523022ce	2025-01-12 05:05:27.207915+02	2025-01-12 05:23:55.634803+02	post/2d5233178f134a9898ce54b4e9029f47.jpg	Unleashing Growth: Helping Businesses Thrive	At GoldOurs, we believe that every business has untapped potential waiting to be discovered	unleashing-growth-helping-businesses-thrive-1	<p>At GoldOurs, we believe that every business has untapped potential waiting to be discovered. The image of a small plant sprouting within a lightbulb perfectly symbolizes our mission: cultivating growth through innovative ideas and nurturing strategies. Just as a seed needs the right environment, resources, and care to thrive, businesses require tailored solutions to uncover their true capabilities.</p>\r\n<p>Our purpose is clear&mdash;to ensure businesses not only grow but also sustain success in an ever-changing market. Growth is not merely about numbers; it's about transforming challenges into opportunities and evolving in ways that create lasting impact. Whether it&rsquo;s through refining internal systems, enhancing leadership, or aligning strategies with future goals, we walk with businesses every step of the way.</p>\r\n<p>Let GoldOurs illuminate your path to growth. Together, we&rsquo;ll turn ideas into action and potential into prosperity, ensuring your business flourishes like the resilient plant in the bulb&mdash;rooted, nurtured, and reaching for the skies.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>	1	65232e6a-fab0-4c2d-920d-59eb9a398865
c6596cb8-e094-4718-9b7a-14ccdcaa75b4	2025-01-22 01:23:26.374206+02	2025-01-22 11:53:46.465143+02	post/3639f51555ea4dd5814a470249c68deb.jpg	The Importance of Talent Management and Development in South African Companies	In today’s competitive business landscape, South African companies are recognizing the critical importance of talent management and development	the-importance-of-talent-management-and-development-in-south-african-companies-1	<p>In today&rsquo;s competitive business landscape, South African companies are recognizing the critical importance of talent management and development. A strong talent management strategy is no longer a luxury&mdash;it&rsquo;s a necessity for businesses striving to remain relevant, innovative, and successful in an ever-changing economic environment.</p>\r\n<p>At GoldOurs, we specialize in helping organizations optimize their workforce through tailored talent management and development solutions, ensuring they not only attract top talent but also retain and nurture it to drive long-term success.</p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3><strong>Why Talent Management is Vital in South Africa</strong></h3>\r\n<p>South Africa faces unique challenges in its workforce, including skills shortages, high unemployment rates, and the need for transformation under the Broad-Based Black Economic Empowerment (B-BBEE) framework. In such a context, effective talent management offers numerous benefits:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Enhancing Organizational Performance</strong><br>Companies that invest in their employees&rsquo; growth see improved productivity, creativity, and overall performance.<br><strong><a title="Talent Management and Development" href="../../../services/talent-management-and-development" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Read more about how employee development impacts business performance.</a></strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Retaining Top Talent</strong><br>With high turnover rates in certain industries, retaining skilled employees is critical. Talent management strategies that focus on employee satisfaction, career growth, and workplace culture help reduce turnover.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Driving Transformation</strong><br>Talent development plays a significant role in advancing South Africa&rsquo;s transformation goals. By upskilling employees and creating opportunities for underrepresented groups, companies can align with B-BBEE goals while fostering diversity.<br><a title="B-BBEE Consulting and Training" href="../../../services/bbbee-consulting-and-training"><strong>Learn about our B-BBEE consulting services</strong>.</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3><strong>GoldOurs&rsquo; Role in Talent Management and Development</strong></h3>\r\n<p>At GoldOurs, we partner with South African companies to design and implement effective talent management strategies. Our services are tailored to meet the unique needs of your organization, ensuring sustainable growth and success.</p>\r\n<h4><strong>1. Identifying Talent Gaps</strong></h4>\r\n<p>We conduct in-depth assessments to identify skills gaps and areas for improvement within your workforce. By understanding these gaps, we create targeted development plans.</p>\r\n<h4><strong>2. Training and Development Programs</strong></h4>\r\n<p>Our customized training solutions equip employees with the skills they need to excel in their roles and adapt to industry changes.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Leadership development programs</li>\r\n<li>Technical skills training</li>\r\n<li>Diversity and inclusion workshops</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4><strong>3. Succession Planning</strong></h4>\r\n<p>GoldOurs helps organizations build robust succession plans, ensuring that leadership and critical roles are always filled with well-prepared, high-performing employees.</p>\r\n<h4><strong>4. B-BBEE-Aligned Talent Development</strong></h4>\r\n<p>We integrate talent development with B-BBEE objectives, helping companies meet compliance requirements while fostering meaningful transformation.<br><strong><a title="B-BBEE Consulting and Training" href="../../../services/bbbee-consulting-and-training" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Explore our B-BBEE-aligned training programs</a>.</strong></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3><strong>The Benefits of Partnering with GoldOurs</strong></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Improved Employee Engagement</strong><br>Engaged employees are more motivated, productive, and loyal. Our strategies focus on aligning employee goals with organizational objectives to maximize engagement.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Long-Term Growth</strong><br>By developing your workforce, we ensure your company is equipped to tackle future challenges and remain competitive.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Compliance Made Simple</strong><br>With our expertise in South African labor laws and B-BBEE requirements, we make compliance effortless for your business.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Enhanced Employer Branding</strong><br>Companies that invest in talent development attract top-tier candidates, reinforcing their reputation as employers of choice.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3><strong>Success Stories: GoldOurs in Action</strong></h3>\r\n<p>At GoldOurs, we&rsquo;ve partnered with numerous South African organizations to transform their talent management strategies. From empowering emerging leaders to creating impactful training programs, we&rsquo;ve seen firsthand how our tailored solutions help businesses thrive.</p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<h3><strong>Looking to Transform Your Workforce?</strong></h3>\r\n<p>GoldOurs is your trusted partner in talent management and development. Let us help you attract, retain, and nurture the talent you need to achieve your business goals.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Contact us today</strong> to schedule a consultation and learn how we can elevate your organization through strategic talent management.<br><strong><a title="Talent Management and Development" href="../../../services/talent-management-and-development" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit our Talent Management Services Page.</a></strong></p>\r\n<hr>\r\n<p>Investing in talent management isn&rsquo;t just about improving your workforce&mdash;it&rsquo;s about securing your company&rsquo;s future. Partner with GoldOurs today and take the first step toward creating a workforce that drives success and transformation.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a title="Goldours Linkedin page" href="https://www.linkedin.com/company/goldours?trk=blended-typeahead">Follow GoldOurs on LinkedIn</a></strong> for more insights on talent management and business growth.</p>	1	62e375f0-94b7-4d43-b3cb-aca1a2957048
5cb33a03-61bd-4dbb-a9d9-e4b93e1f7d70	2025-09-19 19:37:27.323116+02	2025-10-02 11:21:23.811329+02	post/4a5211c3882344ada90c859d3e0905ff.jpg	The 'Why' Behind the Strategy	Does your team feel like it's rowing in different directions, even with a clear strategy? We know it’s a common paradox. At GoldOurs, we believe the biggest challenge is a lack of alignment.	the-why-behind-the-strategy	<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN">Does your team feel like it's rowing in a thousand different directions, even when you have a clear, compelling strategy? You're not alone. This is a paradox that plagues even the most visionary organisations. The most brilliant plans can lead to internal chaos and stalled progress when a shared sense of purpose is missing.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN">At GoldOurs, we believe the biggest challenge isn't a lack of vision; it's a lack of <strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;">alignment</strong>.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style="margin-top: 14.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 13.0pt; line-height: 115%; color: black;">The Problem with "What" Over "Why"</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN">Most strategic planning sessions focus heavily on the "what"&mdash;what are our goals, what are our targets, what are the action items? This is a crucial step, but it&rsquo;s incomplete. A strategy document is just a collection of words on a page until it&rsquo;s brought to life by a unified leadership team.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN">Without a shared "why," each department and team leader will interpret the strategy through their own siloed lens. A sales team might focus on revenue targets, while a product team prioritises new features, and a finance team zeros in on cost-cutting. While each of these goals is valid in isolation, they can quickly become competing priorities that work against each other. The result? Internal friction, wasted resources, and a strategy that never achieves its full potential.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style="margin-top: 14.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 13.0pt; line-height: 115%; color: black;">From Silos to a Cohesive Force</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN">True growth isn&rsquo;t an accident; it's the result of every individual understanding their part in the bigger picture. When every leader is aligned on a single purpose, we&rsquo;ve seen organisations transform from a siloed approach to a cohesive, unified force. This is where strategy becomes more than a document&mdash;it becomes a living, breathing part of your corporate culture.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN">So, how do you achieve this?</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="1" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 12.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN">Start with the Core:</span></strong><span lang="EN"> Revisit your mission, vision, and values. Ensure your strategy is a direct extension of these core principles.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 12.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;">&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN">Communicate Relentlessly:</span></strong><span lang="EN"> Don&rsquo;t just share the strategy; tell the story behind it. Explain the "why" in every meeting, every email, and every team discussion.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;">&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 12.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN">Encourage Dialogue:</span></strong><span lang="EN"> Create a safe space for leaders to challenge assumptions, ask questions, and truly buy into the plan. Alignment isn't about forced compliance; it's about shared conviction.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 12.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 style="margin-top: 14.0pt; mso-pagination: widow-orphan; page-break-after: auto;"><strong style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 13.0pt; line-height: 115%; color: black;">The Power of a Shared Purpose</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN">When you get this right, the benefits are immediate and profound. Decisions are made faster because there&rsquo;s a clear North Star. Resources are allocated more efficiently because everyone understands the priority. And, most importantly, your team moves from a place of simply doing their jobs to actively collaborating on a shared mission.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN">At GoldOurs, we help leaders unlock this power. We believe that by focusing on leadership alignment, you can transform your strategic vision into a high-impact reality, saving you from corporate chaos and setting your organisation on a clear, direct path to success.</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
50b216f9-2332-467d-bc3e-b96b544fba2d	2025-10-02 10:37:21.862912+02	2025-10-02 12:12:47.293849+02	post/213950d6e7724ba1bf642b44e27e6a17.jpg	Solution to misalignment	For us, strategy isn’t just about the “what”.  It’s about the “why”.	solution-to-misalignment	<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">F<strong>or us, strategy isn&rsquo;t just about the &ldquo;what&rdquo;.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>It&rsquo;s about the &ldquo;why&rdquo;.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>When every leader is aligned on a single purpose, we&rsquo;ve seen organisations move from a siloed approach to a cohesive, unified force. True growth isn&rsquo;t an accident.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>It&rsquo;s the result of every individual understanding their part in the bigger picture.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">So let&rsquo;s start at the beginning. Just what is leadership alignment? Goldours explains.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20; mso-no-proof: yes;"><!--[endif]--></span></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">Leadership alignment is when a group of people who share a common set of objectives and agree on the actions required by themselves and their teams to achieve them. </span></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><em><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">Simply put, leadership alignment is when leaders agree on a business strategy <span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial;">and</span>&nbsp;how to execute it. </span></strong></em></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">So why all the hype? </span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #231f20;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">Experts agree that alignment can be a competitive differentiator when leaders align around a shared vision to drive faster and more effective innovation.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #231f20;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">G</span><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; background: white;">lobal management consulting firm McKinsey confirms there is a strong link between </span><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20; background: white;">leadership teams that are aligned and organisations that &ldquo;overperform, or outperform, over long periods of time.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #231f20;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">Others point to a shared vision driving faster and more effective innovation.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">So what are the other rewards?</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">Everyone agrees that all company resources &ndash; human and otherwise &ndash; must be leveraged to maximise benefit. This is what leadership alignment delivers.</span></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #231f20;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">Gibraltar coach Lucia Baldelli says that aligned teams can make fast decisions because all are clear on the priorities, based on shared values and behaviours, and importantly, the corporate strategy.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #231f20;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">Leadership teams are more resilient because they navigate challenges more effectively and can adapt quickly.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 36.0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;">5 steps for maintaining alignment</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #231f20;"><img src="goldours-leadership alignment-5steps" alt=""><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/WbYhFNpd/IMG-20251002-WA0003.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="768"></span></strong></p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">1. <span style="mso-tab-count: 1;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span>Maintain a clear vision and strategy</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: square;">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Ensure leaders are aligned on the company&rsquo;s fundamental vision, mission and core values.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Develop a clear vision for the company that everyone can get behind.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Communicate the strategy well.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">2. <span style="mso-tab-count: 1;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Prioritise communication and collaboration</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 6.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Consistent, open communication and regular feedback loops among leadership and teams encourage understanding and address concerns.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 6.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Encourage cross-functional collaboration to enable leaders from different departments to share updates, address roadblocks, and align priorities.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Implement shared platforms to centralise information, make it easily accessible, and maintain transparency across the company.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">3. <span style="mso-tab-count: 1;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Provide clarity on roles and expectations</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 6.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Ensure that everyone clearly understands their roles, responsibilities, and the expectations associated with their positions.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 6.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Identify and address potential bottlenecks and challenges upfront to smooth out expectations and prevent confusion.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Clearly define what information should be communicated, to whom, when, and how, to ensure consistent messaging across all teams.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">4. <span style="mso-tab-count: 1;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Focus on a culture of trust and accountability</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 6.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Publicly state that dissenting opinions are welcome, thereby fostering a healthy environment that promotes better decision-making and growth.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 6.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Cultivate an environment of trust and psychological safety, empowering individuals to speak up when issues arise.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Establish clear expectations and ensure leaders are accountable for enforcing them, promoting a culture of mutual accountability at all levels.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">5. <span style="mso-tab-count: 1;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Ensure ongoing leadership development&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 6.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Invest in leadership development programmes that focus on shared learning and collaborative problem-solving.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 6.0pt 36.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Use tools and feedback mechanisms, such as assessments, to pinpoint leadership strengths and identify areas for development.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Use regular check-ins, feedback loops, and assessments to maintain consistency and alignment throughout the leadership hierarchy.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">For details on how Goldours can assist you and your business, contact Sazi Ndwandwa on (email) <a href="mailto:sazi@goldours.co.za">sazi@goldours.co.za</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: #001d35; letter-spacing: .1pt; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">If you like this blog, please share and follow us on <a title="LinkedIn Goldours" href="https://bit.ly/4o4RIW9" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>. </span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
9e6b7692-945a-40d1-ac11-49088337c165	2025-10-11 18:17:42.938423+02	2025-10-11 19:05:27.41368+02	post/c38602e56aca421c81cc7411aa1e5c22.jpeg	Transform your vision into a unified, high-impact reality	We want to know: What's the biggest challenge you have faced when trying to get your team on the same page with the new strategy? A lack of buy-in? Competing priorities? Share your experiences below.	transform-your-vision-into-a-unified-high-impact-reality	<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><strong><span lang="EN-US">At GoldOurs, we believe that with a shared 'why', a strategy is just a document. We also share what the experts say is the best roadmap to transforming your vision into a unified, high-impact reality in our new article.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">Before we delve into the details, corporate leaders recognise that there is a compelling case for ensuring that their corporate vision becomes a reality.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">It is borne out by Harvard writers <a href="ttps://hbr.org/2005/07/turning-great-strategy-into-great-performance">Michael Mankins and Richard Steele, </a>who say that if management were to realise the full potential of its current strategy, the increase in value could be as much as 60% to 100%. For any corporation, the size of the reward is very much worth the effort. The surveyed leaders agree.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">So do we.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>But what is clear is that there isn&rsquo;t one right version. Just as all corporates differ in their vision, goals, and objectives, so do the strategies for achieving corporate strategy.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">What is equally clear is that it is easier said than done. The Harvard writing duo, with a formidable pedigree in consulting firms, attribute the strategy-to-performance gap to a combination of factors, including poorly formulated plans, the misapplication of resources, breakdowns in communication, and limited accountability for results.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">They estimate, based on executive feedback, that the failure to have the right resources in the right place at the right time strips away some 7,5% of the strategy's potential value. Some 5,2% is lost to poor communication, 4,5% to poor action planning, 4,1% to blurred accountabilities, and so on.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">Goldours has reviewed several frameworks and plans.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>There is an interesting variety of frameworks and plans for achieving a strategy. Some, like Rhythms Systems, make a lot of sense.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">It advocates a <a href="https://www.rhythmsystems.com/blog/strategy-execution-guide">7-point framework</a>:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/V6YMVYzZ/TURNING-VISION-1.jpg"></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><img src="https://postimg.cc/yJbkJCg0" alt=""></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><img src="https://postimg.cc/3WGDDzxG" alt=""><em><strong><span lang="EN-US">Figure 1: Rhythm&rsquo;s 7-point plan</span></strong></em></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">They also offer a helpful free strategy execution assessment <a href="https://www.rhythmsystems.com/organizational-effectiveness-test?hsCtaTracking=965d5acb-cdc4-45ab-8616-494f0c47e323%7C27b13648-9fd6-4bbc-870b-253b9b2f0c6e">here</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">Other business consultants like <a href="https://gabrieltopman.com/transforming-your-vision-to-reality/">Gabriel Topman</a> provide a more detailed approach:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/G2cY5cb7/TURNING-VISION-3.jpg" alt=""></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><img src="https://postimg.cc/Nyz5yv9m" alt=""></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><img src="https://postimg.cc/3WGDDzxG" alt=""><em><strong><span lang="EN-US">Figure 2: Gabriel Topman's 10-step plan</span></strong></em></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span lang="EN-US">What will work for you? And how will this help address the biggest challenge you have faced?</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
abe581f7-e993-4ba6-965f-e093ac0f1d7f	2025-10-19 18:05:09.552118+02	2025-10-19 18:20:57.634736+02	post/783c6f352c5743b3917401861d768db2.jpeg	A culture of accountability: Our businesses need it.	We set ambitious goals and track the numbers, but still fall short.  The gap between setting a target and achieving it is often a lack of real accountability.  Simply having goals isn’t enough.	a-culture-of-accountability-our-businesses-need-it	<p class="MsoNormal"><em><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">We set ambitious goals and track the numbers, but still fall short.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>The gap between setting a target and achieving it is often a lack of real accountability.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Simply having goals isn&rsquo;t enough.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>You need a culture that fuels momentum.</span></em></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><em><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Discover why it is important to go beyond static metrics and build a team that owns its results in our latest article.</span></em></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">I came across a post today that made me stop in my tracks. Culture beats strategy every time. As someone who advocated for both, it was a landing I needed after pulling out all the stops this week to deliver quality outputs.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">But I needed my team to pull together to be able to do it; we used our unique set of cultural ingredients of drive, accountability and respect for our client&rsquo;s goals as well as our own to get the job done.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Surprisingly, once these culture drivers are embedded in your work ethos, work becomes less of a job and much more about passion and commitment. The job almost becomes effortless.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">But that&rsquo;s enough on that topic for now.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">For this week&rsquo;s blog, I looked to see what other resources affirmed the thinking of the Goldours&rsquo; accountability culture, and it being instrumental in delivering quality results.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">It didn&rsquo;t take long. Some of you are familiar with Betterworks. For those who aren&rsquo;t, it <span style="background: white;">is an enterprise-grade performance management software platform.</span></span><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Their 2023 <span style="color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; text-decoration: none; text-underline: none;">State of Performance Enablement report</span><span style="font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; widows: 2; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; float: none; word-spacing: 0px;"> points to &ldquo;employee engagement and productivity soar when accountability is embedded within workplace systems. Employees who receive fair and unbiased performance management processes can accept criticism and apply what they&rsquo;ve learned</span>&rdquo;.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">But there is a powerful knock-on benefit for a team. Accountability builds trust within teams, as we rely on and trust each other to deliver the results so that we reach the end goal.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Betterworks says accountability also helps motivate the workforce. Employees who are held accountable are more likely to take ownership of their work. And the results - increased job satisfaction, higher morale, and improved team performance.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Experts like Betterworks also point to healthy accountability, creating an environment where mistakes are opportunities for growth and learning, rather than failures to be punished. And that has to be good for everyone.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">The cultural environment for accountability is also evidenced by:</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">An environment where team members can honestly and openly discuss progress, challenges, and mistakes without fear of shame</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Members rely on each other's strengths and provide mutual support to overcome obstacles </span></p>\r\n<p style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white; vertical-align: baseline; margin: 0cm 0cm 0cm 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Team members address accountability issues directly and constructively with each other.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">And the benefits? Five benefits are highlighted: High performance, boosts morale and commitment, fosters trust, improves problem-solving and supports development.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">For this week&rsquo;s blog, I have taken a slightly more conversational approach.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Please let me know what you think of the approach and what value you found in this edition.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>I am interested.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Have a good week!</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
4deb3ce9-a718-4b0a-9340-50d9dcedd421	2025-10-25 14:26:43.765697+02	2025-10-25 14:40:50.801033+02	post/c738c13bd5e34d03b762862ba66d1ea6.png	Transforming team culture	At Goldours, we know accountability can be misunderstood. We redefine it as ownership & transparency. When accountability is a shared commitment, it becomes a powerful engine for innovation & growth.	transforming-team-culture-1	<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">While reviewing the material I wanted to include in this Goldours&rsquo; blog, I came across the insightful <a href="https://culturepartners.com/insights/how-to-successfully-change-the-culture-of-a-team/">Culture Partners</a> content. Formerly Partners In Leadership, it was founded in 1989 by authors of the NY Times best-selling books, <a href="https://www.google.co.za/books/edition/The_Oz_Principle/3GyWWjiWz2sC?hl=en&amp;gbpv=1&amp;pg=PT13&amp;printsec=frontcover">The Oz Principle</a> and <a href="https://www.google.co.za/books/edition/Change_the_Culture_Change_the_Game/3q9iAQREqE8C?hl=en&amp;gbpv=1&amp;pg=PT4&amp;printsec=frontcover">Change the Culture, Change the Game</a></span><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">The current chief strategy officer, Dr Jessica Kriegel, says that &ldquo;organisations fully aligned on purpose, strategy, and culture average a +44.5% change in revenue growth over three years.&rdquo;*</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/rFV30sZz/BLOG-TEXT.png" alt="" width="705" height="491"></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">That&rsquo;s impressive.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">What&rsquo;s more, she explains, the more you align your culture with your purpose and strategy, the more you&rsquo;ll gain business advantage.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">So while culture may not be important <em>per se</em> to investments, revenue growth is, and so all efforts to improve an accountability culture are particularly relevant.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">And we are also talking about accountability at the leadership level.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&ldquo;One for all and all for one,&rdquo; a motto of The Three Musketeers, which means that the group will act as a united front to support and protect each other. The phrase symbolises their strong bond of brotherhood and loyalty. Not too different from what is required in a business.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">So how does one create a culture of accountability?</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/DwgrMQqN/Goldours-changing-culture.png" alt="" width="716" height="403"></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">As with most organisational activities, culture change doesn&rsquo;t happen overnight. It is a process that consists of five steps, as shown below. And at its centre is leadership that must drive the change.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">A <a href="https://online.hbs.edu/blog/post/ethics-and-accountability-in-the-workplace">Harvard article, penned by Esther Han</a>, says that creating a leadership culture of accountability is evidenced by five behaviours:</span></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 6.0pt; margin-bottom: 6.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Leading by example.</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"> Leaders must lead by example and demonstrate the behaviours they want to see in the organisation.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 6.0pt; margin-bottom: 6.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Providing meaningful feedback</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">. Gallup research shows that regular, meaningful feedback is four times more likely to lead to engagement.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 6.0pt; margin-bottom: 6.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Combating workplace bias. </span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Particularly important for South Africa, I support the thinking and practice of building a culture of ethics and accountability because it means people must proactively combat bias and stereotypes.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 6.0pt; margin-bottom: 6.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Giving employees a voice</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">. While this process is not easy or comfortable, it is proactive and involves really listening to others. But it does mean that you should be able to increase employee satisfaction and reduce costly staff turnover.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 6.0pt; margin-bottom: 6.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Developing an authentic leadership style</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">. Your leadership style will effectively demonstrate your values, principles, and mission.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">This blog has touched on the important topic of culture. There is a lot to discuss to help organisations embrace ethical practices across the public and private sectors. It&rsquo;s a topic that needs much more discussion, particularly among leaders and their teams, to embrace processes that will help guard against this scourge. As in the words of Desmond Tutu, &ldquo;if you are neutral in situations of injustice (or corruption), you have chosen the side of the oppressor (corruption)&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">(*Culture Partners and Stanford Research 2023)</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
c0bd67eb-b9d3-4a3d-b15e-10e5ae08065a	2025-11-02 16:09:21.368904+02	2025-11-02 16:15:47.257279+02	post/988a03ce5a3b4e7eadb942436327f0a1.png	Ownership: Can it deliver high-level accountability?	What's one thing your organisation does to foster a sense of ownership in the team? Building a high-accountability culture is a continuous effort.	ownership-can-it-deliver-high-level-accountability-1	<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">For true success, ownership and accountability form a crucial partnership, as they foster a culture of responsibility that leads to improved decision-making, increased productivity, and greater trust. Goldours agrees.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">So what&rsquo;s the difference? Ownership is a proactive commitment to completing the task and achieving its outcome.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">On the other hand, accountability is the responsibility for the results.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Together, these principles empower individuals and teams to achieve higher performance, engage more deeply with their work, and learn from mistakes to drive continuous improvement.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">So let&rsquo;s take a closer look at the characteristics of these two powerhouses:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Ownership: Taking initiative and pride</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #001d35; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Proactive mindset: Owners don't wait for direction; they take initiative and act as if they are the organisation.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #001d35; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Commitment:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>It goes beyond simply completing a task to being invested in the overall success of the project or goal.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #001d35; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Problem-solving:&nbsp;It transforms a problem from "not my problem" to "my opportunity to solve it".&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Accountability: Being answerable for the results</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #001d35; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Follow-through:&nbsp;It is the commitment to deliver on promises, on time and to the required standard.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #001d35; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Taking responsibility means being accountable for both successes and setbacks.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #001d35; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Measuring outcomes provides a framework for evaluating and learning from the actions and decisions made.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 9.0pt 18.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Let&rsquo;s examine the benefits for individuals, teams, and organisations.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 9.0pt 18.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/kM2jLQ6w/Builds-trust-and-collaboration.jpg" alt="" width="810" height="456"></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white; margin: 0cm 0cm 9.0pt 18.0pt;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">How have you experienced this duo in your organisation?&nbsp; The more we share, the more we learn.</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
953d9301-111f-46b0-a529-2001e5e9f6a9	2025-11-10 13:32:51.87571+02	2025-11-10 14:16:40.018427+02	post/42e595da96bf4ba685cfcdbdf267ee55.jpeg	ROI of compliance: How good governance can help you win	Too many businesses view compliance as a cost. At GoldOurs, we believe not only does it significantly minimise business risk, but it is also a competitive advantage to advance the business.	roi-of-compliance-how-good-governance-can-help-you-win	<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN;">Too many businesses view compliance as a cost. At GoldOurs, we believe not only does it significantly minimise business risk, but it is also a competitive advantage to advance the business.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN;">Let&rsquo;s take a closer look at the benefits, as well as financial metrics, to help do a better job. Read our next blog.</span><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Arial; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-ansi-language: EN;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">Compliance in South Africa involves adhering to various legal and regulatory requirements,&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;"><span style="box-sizing: border-box;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">including the&nbsp;</span>Companies Act<span style="font-size: 11pt;">,</span>&nbsp;the<span style="font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</span>Broad-Based Economic Empowerment Act<span style="font-size: 11pt;">,&nbsp;</span>the Protection of Personal Information Act<span style="font-size: 11pt;">, and the Financial Intelligence Centre Act (which addresses </span></span>anti-money laundering). In some sectors, businesses must also comply with their sector-specific regulations, health and safety laws, and financial reporting obligations. Goldours shares its insights on how to transform onerous compliance into a competitive advantage.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">The benefits of compliance encompass<span style="background: white;"> both <strong><em>quantitative</em></strong> and qualitative gains, including cost savings and increased earnings. <strong><em>Qualitative</em></strong> benefits include an enhanced reputation, brand value, and greater trust. </span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">A strong compliance programme ensures that risks, such as fines and reputational damage, are minimised.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">If one takes it further, compliance can also provide a competitive advantage, making it a strategic investment rather than a cost centre.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;"><a href="https://www.navex.com/en-us/blog/article/the-compliance-balancing-act-how-less-complexity-can-mean-more-roi/">Navex, a leading American authority on governance, risk, and compliance,</a> states that organisations centralising their compliance programmes can reduce administrative overhead by as much as&nbsp;</span><strong><span style="color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;">20%</span></strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; background: white;">. This doesn&rsquo;t just free up resources &ndash; it redirects them toward growth and innovation.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">It's not an insignificant number. So let&rsquo;s take a closer look at the benefits:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Quantitative benefits</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Cost savings</span></strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">:&nbsp;Preventing violations, conflicts, and fines can result in annual savings of millions of dollars.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Increased earnings:</span></strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Compliance can lead to higher profits by increasing efficiency and allowing more time for strategic initiatives.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 36.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Qualitative benefits</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Enhanced reputation:</span></strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"> A strong compliance programme builds trust with stakeholders and improves professional reputation.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Competitive advantage:</span></strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Compliance can differentiate a company and provide the ability to pursue new business opportunities.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Risk mitigation:</span></strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"> It directly reduces the risk of financial penalties, legal issues, and other consequences that arise from non-compliance.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Long-term mission success:</span></strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Compliance ensures the business is operating sustainably, contributing to its long-term goals.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">And what financial metrics matter?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Four are listed by <a href="https://www.complianceandrisks.com/blog/cfos-are-demanding-compliance-roi-the-4-financial-metrics-that-actually-matter-in-2025/">Compliance &amp; Risks</a>, which operates in the United States and EMEA:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/D06QcJKP/Financial-indicator-Compliance-ROI.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720"></span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
6e5ade24-4e31-4980-9393-95408cfab64a	2025-11-18 09:15:54.643525+02	2025-11-18 09:18:01.624519+02	post/17edf980d20c4a2391f6efb92b845016.jpeg	Corporate governance: Costly compliance or strategic lever?	While corporate governance may be perceived as merely a matter of compliance, it is so much more.	corporate-governance-costly-compliance-or-strategic-lever	<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">At first glance, corporate governance may be perceived as merely a matter of compliance. While compliance is necessary, corporate governance can be fine-tuned into a strategic lever for sustainable success, allowing a business to navigate a myriad of business complexities, manage risks, and position the organisation to take advantage of future opportunities.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">Goldours agrees that weak governance is a significant risk, and its impact can be considerable on the business, leading to poor stakeholder confidence, erosion of value, and damage to reputational risk. </span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">However, good governance has <a href="(https:/goldours.co.za/article/roi-of-compliance-how-good-governance-can-help-you-win)">significant benefits</a> that extend beyond reducing risk.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">Its benefits are both quantitative and qualitative, ranging from attracting investors and lowering capital costs to enhancing reputation and trust, driving sustainable growth and performance, improving risk management and resilience, facilitating effective decision-making, and ensuring legal and regulatory compliance.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">Global consulting firm <a href="https://www.mercer.com/en-us/insights/investments/outsourced-cio-ocio/the-role-of-good-governance-in-shaping-organizational-outcomes">Mercer</a> </span><span style="color: #0e101a;">agrees and explains that organisations need to reframe corporate governance as an accelerator, not a brake.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">When they do so, corporate governance becomes a powerful tool for gaining a competitive advantage, as they can move faster, act smarter, and capitalise on opportunities.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">However, to achieve this, one needs a strategic framework that aligns with the organisation&rsquo;s vision, mission, values, and objectives.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">Mercer advocates a three-step process for the design process: Assess, design, and implement.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/85NT97PJ/A-strategic-framework-for-corporate-governance-(2).jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720"></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">However, let&rsquo;s not forget that compliance can also serve as a strategic lever for achieving high performance.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">It should be good news for the nearly 74% of organisations that view compliance as a burden, something to &ldquo;get through&rdquo; rather than an opportunity to improve, according to the Finnish e-learning platform and training provider <a href="https://www.techclass.com/resources/learning-and-development-articles/turning-compliance-training-into-strategic-advantage?srsltid=AfmBOoo0y4f5ycUZzvlHQN4w-sQ2Shsq29hHGXSQ6OPWGxIDh1-ZjeOp">Techclass</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">They believe that compliance often encodes </span>best practices that align with smart business operations<span style="color: #0e101a;"> and </span>operational excellence<span style="color: #0e101a;">.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">Techclass says that leaders are increasingly embracing this perspective. According to recent surveys, </span>73% of executives believe that meeting compliance standards enhances how stakeholders perceive their company, among other benefits<span style="color: #0e101a;">.</span></p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;"><span style="color: #0e101a;">It believes that compliance is&nbsp;</span>integral to the company&rsquo;s mission and success.</p>\r\n<p style="margin: 0cm;">For more insights, go <a href="https://bit.ly/4nV416J">here</a>.</p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
33d4fb5e-4e82-4940-9aac-ea0af72681f3	2025-11-24 18:59:49.164213+02	2025-11-24 19:00:19.51121+02	post/67b704b538d44671bc85fb4f1d6230fb.jpeg	The strategic link to tenders	In tender situations, what gives you the edge? Beyond your service/product, a strong commitment to compliance signals trustworthiness and a shared vision for social and economic transformation.	the-strategic-link-to-tenders	<p style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">One of the biggest drivers of compliance in South Africa, and in particular black economic empowerment (BBBEE), is access to government spending. It&rsquo;s a client that very few businesses can ignore, with total consolidated government spending projected to increase nominally to R2,6 trillion by 2026/27.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Compliance &ndash; regulatory and otherwise, including BBBEE - is indicative of the organisation being a responsible, trustworthy and committed to the country&rsquo;s transformation agenda.</span></p>\r\n<p style="background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">The BBBEE agenda includes:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1;">Points earned across these elements determine your BBBEE level (from Level 1 to Level 8):</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 2; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/fbKWsZJK/GOLDOURS-BBBEE-CATEGORIES.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720">Figure 1</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 2; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">But what benefits does BBBEE compliance mean for South African businesses in securing government business?</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">1. Competitive edge in procurement and tenders</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Many state-owned and aligned organisations will give preference to those who score well on broad-based black empowerment. It may rule out some low-scoring organisations.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">2. Access to financial and tax incentives</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Compliant businesses will have access to grants, tax deductions, and incentives.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">3. Enhanced reputation and stakeholder trust</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">BBBEE compliance demonstrates an organisation&rsquo;s commitment to transformation and social justice with its stakeholders.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">4. Attraction and retention of talent</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">A proactive, transformative stance toward its people will attract and retain the best talent. </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-outline-level: 3; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">5. Contribution to national transformation</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Segoe UI'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Each scorecard element contributes to a more equitable economy, fulfilling the moral and legislative obligations to shape a positive future.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Lastly, given the importance of compliance to businesses, what can organisations do to build commitment to compliance?</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/C1gvGTNP/Goldours-how-to-build-compliance.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720"></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-themecolor: text1; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Figure 2</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
6c63e795-abfa-4244-b4d5-0ea3d0a92425	2025-12-02 12:28:48.591266+02	2025-12-02 13:17:17.716057+02	post/161d390d399f484a84c1a39a35637a77.jpeg	The shift from managing to empowering	Stop managing people. Start empowering leaders. At GoldOurs, we see the future of leadership as coaching your team for high-impact execution.	the-shift-from-managing-to-empowering	<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif;">Stop managing people. Start empowering leaders. The old "command and control" model stifles innovation and disengages talent. At GoldOurs, we see the future of leadership as coaching your team for high-impact execution.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif;">Typical for-profit businesses &ndash; from small start-ups to major corporations &ndash; measure success through demonstrated revenue and profits (Blank and Dorf, 2012). In contrast, impact-driven businesses prioritise decisions, effort and resources based on the impact the work is having, understanding that profitability may be less as a result (Shaw, 2022). Success for impact-driven businesses lies in balancing measurable impact improvements with financial performance.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif;">So what is high-impact coaching? Impact coaching, according to the US coaching firm Evolve Impact, aims to support leadership authenticity, openness, and coordination among siloed business units, and to integrate profit-and-purpose initiatives throughout the organisation&rsquo;s culture.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif;">Nearly 50% of younger workers don&rsquo;t believe their company will survive another 10 years if there isn&rsquo;t a significant change.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif;">Let&rsquo;s take a closer look at the key strategies for high-impact execution coaching:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/XvhGB7V9/Goldours-managing-empowering-2025.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720"></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Foster psychological safety and trust; set an example</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Create an environment where team members feel safe to share ideas, ask questions, admit mistakes, and take calculated risks without fear of retribution. Building trust through honesty, transparency, and empathy is foundational, so model the behaviours you expect from your team.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Set clear</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><strong>, aligned goals</strong>: Ensure every team member understands their role and how their&nbsp;tasks contribute to the organisation's overarching strategic objectives. Use frameworks like <strong>SMART</strong> goals (Specific, measurable, attainable, relevant, time-bound) or <strong>OKRs</strong> (Objectives and key results) to provide clarity and direction.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Empower and delegate effectively</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Avoid micromanaging; instead, delegate meaningful responsibilities that play to employees' strengths and offer "stretch opportunities" for growth. Provide the necessary resources, support, and autonomy, and be willing to let them learn from failure.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Provide continuous, constructive feedback</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Move away from annual reviews to a rhythm of regular, informal check-ins. Feedback should be specific, actionable, and focused on behaviours rather than personality. The "70-30 rule" suggests aiming for 70% positive reinforcement and 30% growth-focused feedback.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Ask powerful, open-ended questions</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Encourage critical thinking and problem-solving by asking questions that prompt self-discovery, rather than immediately providing answers. Examples include:</span></li>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="circle">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">"What's your initial thinking on this?"</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">"What options are you considering?"</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">"What would success look like in this scenario?"</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Encourage collaboration and communication</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Facilitate an open dialogue that values diverse perspectives, fostering innovation and creative problem-solving. Leverage collaboration tools and cross-functional projects to strengthen working relationships and knowledge sharing.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Promote continuous learning</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Foster a culture that sees challenges as opportunities to learn and grow. Invest in professional development through workshops, peer-to-peer learning, and mentorship programs to build a resilient and adaptable team.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Set an example</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Model the behaviours you expect to see in your team. Your own actions, such as staying calm under pressure, seeking feedback, and maintaining a strong work ethic, significantly influence team culture and engagement.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Measure progress and ensure accountability</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Use clear metrics (KPIs, OKRs) to track progress toward goals. Establish a regular accountability cadence, such as weekly "WIG" (wildly important g</span><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">oals) sessions, in which the team reviews the scoreboard, shares progress, and sets new commitments.</span></li>\r\n</ul>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
737162e2-81b8-48dc-aaaa-73f60040ab53	2025-12-08 11:33:40.695425+02	2025-12-08 11:49:58.725978+02	post/9af3ad1c746a4198b47b0259c7b73380.jpeg	Transitioning from manager to mentor	Stop managing people. Start empowering leaders. At GoldOurs, the future of leadership is coaching your team rather than controlling them.	transitioning-from-manager-to-mentor-1	<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: Aptos, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The shift from managing to empowering.Text: Stop managing people. Start empowering leaders. The old "command and control" model stifles innovation and disengages talent. At GoldOurs, we see the future of leadership as coaching your team rather than controlling them.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">A leader as a coach&nbsp;guides, develops, and empowers team members by asking questions, providing feedback, and fostering self-reliance rather than just issuing orders. This approach focuses on unlocking individual potential, improving performance, and building capability through mentorship, collaboration, and continuous learning.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Key roles of a leader as a coach</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/fLz74D31/Goldours-Key-roles-of-a-leader-as-a-coach-2.png" alt="" width="1279" height="603"></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Key steps to transition</span></strong></p>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="1" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Shift focus (Manager vs mentor)</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="1" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo2; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Manager:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Directs, solves problems, focuses on tasks/output.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="1" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo3; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Mentor:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Guides, empowers, and focuses on individual growth, skills, and goals.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="2" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Adopt a growth mindset &amp; empathy</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="2" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo4; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">See team members as capable of developing; be empathetic to their challenges.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="3" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Ask, don't just tell (guide)</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="3" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo5; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Use open-ended questions (for example, "What do you think could be done differently?") to encourage critical thinking rather than immediate solutions.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="4" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Listen actively &amp; build relationships</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="4" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo6; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Show genuine interest in their goals or challenges beyond work tasks.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="5" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Share experiences (authenticity)</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="5" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo7; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Be transparent about your own successes and failures to show that growth is a journey.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="6" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Empower &amp; delegate (autonomy)</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="6" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo8; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Give team members ownership and increasing responsibility with support, fostering confidence.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="7" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Provide developmental feedback</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="7" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo9; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Offer constructive, specific feedback focusing on behaviours, not just outcomes.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="8" type="1">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Celebrate growth</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol style="margin-top: 0cm;" start="8" type="1">\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo10; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Recognise effort and milestones, not just final results, to boost morale.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo10; tab-stops: list 72.0pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">To read our other blogs, go to https://bit.ly/4iIz6K7</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
8b417bcb-283f-436f-913b-f0358f367abf	2025-12-17 19:07:15.07804+02	2025-12-17 19:07:23.576066+02	post/4e8cce7434314a18a131f7d32d600f41.jpeg	Weekly Nuggets: No 1: 12 December 2025	Welcome to our weekly nuggets, where we share some insights from our work with clients. In this edition, we focus on corporate governance.	weekly-nuggets-no-1-12-december-2025-1	<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Weekly Nuggets</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><a name="_Toc191465416"></a><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Nugget 1:</span></strong><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;12 December 2026</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Welcome to our weekly nuggets, where we share some insights from our work with clients.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">This was a busy week. We had proposals to submit for a few public sector RFQs; we were chasing to complete our accounting work before closing off the year; we had executive and business coaching sessions; we even had a meeting with a client that we had been servicing since November 2022 to prioritise what we can continue to support them with because the amount of time and B-BBEE expertise they required no longer aligned with the fees we had negotiated &ndash; it was a wonderful negotiation that was quickly resolved because of&nbsp;long-standing relationship and needs-understanding we had built.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">What I want to highlight is a performance evaluation we completed for the governance committees of a public sector entity.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Context <span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">The governance committee's three-year tenures were coming to an end. The client needed an evaluation to help decide on which members&rsquo; terms to renew and also general feedback on how effectively the committees had implemented their respective charters.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Approach</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">We designed a customised approach after understanding the entity&rsquo;s legal and strategic context. Our methodology consisted of three data collection methods:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">A qualitative implementation checklist against the charter requirements</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Designing an online survey with questions based on PFMA expectations for the Audit &amp; Risk Committee, together with expectations from the charters. The surveys were distributed to all the members of management, the internal audit team, the external auditors, and all the members of the governance charters</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Follow up semi-structured interviews using a smaller sample, excluding the external auditors.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; line-height: 106%;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Once the data was collected, we analysed it and identified strengths and areas for improvement both at the committee level and for each member. We identified eight governance themes, including the composition of the governance committee (e.g., demographics, skills, experience, operational expertise), independence and ethics, risk management, performance management, succession planning (at the governance committee and management levels), communication, inter-committee alignment, and the effectiveness of individual members.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Outcome</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">We delivered a report that was essentially a master&rsquo;s dissertation, including a bibliography and a reliability analysis (the survey had a 70% response rate). The most important thing was that we delivered a service that met and exceeded the client&rsquo;s expectations. For instance, we identified areas of strength that should be safeguarded; we identified the root causes for areas that need improvement (including strengthening secretarial support); and we provided a predictive framework that can be used at the appointment stage to ensure that each governance committee has the required balance of ingredients for it to be effective.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Lessons for those who serve on governance committees</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Although this exercise was for our client, some lesson points that may be useful to a broader audience. The client has reviewed this article and given permission for us to share, though we have taken measures to ensure anonymity.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">We identified the following factors to consider when forming governance boards or sub-committees. The emphasis is on balance and not requiring any one person to have all of these ingredients:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Relevant academic qualifications, relevant executive experience, or relevant non-executive experience.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Relevant professional body membership and designation (e.g. for Audit Committees membership with professional bodies such as SAICA, SAIGA, IIA, ISACA; for Human Capital or Remuneration committees membership with professional bodies such as SABPP &amp; IPM).</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Sufficient relevant executive or senior management experience, which enables the members to oversee and practically guide the executive team at the required level of seniority and technical understanding.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Operational understanding of the organisation's business gives the board and sub-committees industry-specific insights and referral networks.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">We believe in ongoing induction of board members, together with their own personal pursuit of an ever-growing understanding of the organisation, its mandate, and its business context.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 35.45pt; text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">This induction includes ensuring that the members and the chairperson are suitably equipped through training (this is often assumed) and role clarification; and, above all,</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8.0pt 35.45pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 106%; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Always be aware of the responsibility you automatically attract and carry for the organisation&rsquo;s ethical tone, including building a relationship of common purpose with the executive team. Examples include preparing for meetings, contributing during meetings, and avoiding a pattern of small, unprofessional behaviours, such as being late to meetings, missing calendar invitations, not responding to official communications, such as emails, and adopting a tone that may not align with mutual respect between the non-executive and executive directors.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 106%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; margin: 0cm 0cm 8.0pt 35.45pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">In Summary</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">We enjoyed the exercise and were happy that we added value to our client. We were reminded of the important role that governance bodies play in sustainable organisational success &ndash; regardless of sector or industry. The selection of suitable governance body members, the quality of their induction, and constant self-evaluation against their charter cannot be overemphasised. The chairperson of any governance body carries the primary leadership role, which necessitates intentional stakeholder management within the governing body, with the chief executive, other governing body chairs, and as a public ambassador for the organisation.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">About the Author</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Sazi Ndwandwa has been a chartered accountant since 2008. He has been leading experienced, qualified senior managers since 2014. He holds an MPhil degree in leadership coaching and serves on a few boards as a non-executive director. Sazi has a passion for sustainable transformational growth and acknowledges that Black Empowerment Policies have ensured that, together with relational support, his talents and work ethic give him access to opportunity, contribution, and recognition.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">About the GoldOurs</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">We are a one-stop sustainable growth service centre, offering integrated services. We are a team of qualified and experienced subject matter experts. Our four service pillars are: Governance &amp; Direction; Talent Management &amp; Development; Accounting, Tax &amp; Assurance; and B-BBEE Consulting &amp; Training.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: black; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">We are a level 1 B-BBEE contributor (100% black-owned).</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
748fa4e4-fa67-4b43-9dd7-15edcdc8610b	2025-12-17 19:25:29.159388+02	2025-12-17 19:32:37.444412+02	post/fc01c75c6151466a8f139c7fc385ee32.jpeg	The impact of empowered teams	By providing autonomy and fostering a safe space for learning and risk-taking, you’re building a resilient and adaptable workforce.	the-impact-of-empowered-teams	<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 12.0pt 0cm 12.0pt 0cm;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif;">Micromanagement is a relic of the past. By providing autonomy and fostering a safe space for learning and risk-taking, you&rsquo;re building a resilient and adaptable workforce.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><span style="font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-bidi; mso-ansi-language: EN-ZA; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">Explore how coaching your team for high-impact execution can transform your business.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Empowered teams, characterised by their <strong>autonomy, accountability, and cross-functional nature</strong>, can deliver significant value to companies, ranging from&nbsp;accelerated innovation to increased profitability. They are given the authority to make decisions and own outcomes, rather than execute tasks assigned by management.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">In essence, empowered teams transform a company from a "feature factory" that measures output to an outcome-focused organisation that delivers meaningful impact for both customers and the business.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Here are the key benefits empowered teams can deliver:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Enhanced business performance &amp; outcomes&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Accelerated innovation and creativity</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: By fostering an environment where teams feel safe exploring new ideas, taking risks, and experimenting, companies can achieve greater innovation.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Faster problem-solving and decision-making</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Teams that can make decisions without waiting for top-down approval are more agile, resolving issues faster and adapting to changes more quickly.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Improved speed to market</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Autonomy enables teams to move with momentum, delivering value early and often through iterative processes, thereby shortening feedback loops and reducing risk.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Increased profitability</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Companies with high levels of employee engagement and empowerment have significantly higher profitability than those with low engagement.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Better, customer-centric solutions</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Empowered product teams are focused on solving customer problems and driving specific outcomes, leading to products and services that better meet customer needs and improve total customer satisfaction.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 15.0pt; font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #001d35; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">People &amp; culture benefits</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Higher employee engagement and motivation</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: When people have autonomy, the ability to master new skills, and a clear purpose, their intrinsic motivation increases, leading to higher, more sustainable performance.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Greater accountability and ownership</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Teams take full ownership of their work and outcomes, both successes and failures, because they are trusted to make the right decisions.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Improved talent attraction and retention</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: A culture that trusts and empowers its employees is more attractive to top talent and boosts loyalty and job satisfaction, reducing employee turnover.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Stronger culture of trust and collaboration</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: The shift from a command-and-control dynamic to one of coaching and trust fosters open communication, collaboration, and psychological safety within and across teams.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Continuous learning and growth</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">: Empowered teams are encouraged to learn continuously from data, feedback, and experimentation, contributing to a company-wide culture of continuous improvement.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="color: rgb(10, 10, 10); margin-bottom: 9pt; line-height: 18pt; background-image: initial; background-position-x: initial; background-position-y: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Aptos',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">To read our other blogs, go to https://bit.ly/4iIz6K7</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
c349c347-d4de-4fec-86fc-473fac414b38	2026-01-31 14:40:12.863381+02	2026-01-31 14:40:12.863408+02	post/ff465b42690540f9a62b3d48c8989936.jpeg	ROI of social impact	Can doing good be good for business? At GoldOurs, we know when your CSI is strategically aligned with your core values, it's a powerful engine for brand growth, talent attraction, and profitability.	roi-of-social-impact	<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Look at any of the South African reports, and you find a section highlighting the organisation&rsquo;s corporate social investment. It is fair to say that they are no slouches with investments estimated at over R13 billion in 2025.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">So, it is important that the community investments deliver on the so-called benefits: increased revenue and retention, reduced customer acquisition costs, product innovation and feedback, including strengthened brand equity.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"><img src="https://postimg.cc/SJTVwrJ7" alt=""></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/QdsPKYDP/Orange-Yellow-and-Grey-Simple-Project-Lifecycle-Presentation.jpg" alt="" width="733" height="412"></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><a href="https://www.forbes.com/councils/forbesbusinesscouncil/2026/01/22/17-ways-to-measure-roi-from-culture-trust-and-social-impact/">Forbes</a>&nbsp;</span><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">published an editorial earlier this year that included insights from its exclusive, invitation-only business council. They listed 17 ways to assess the ROI of social impact, brand trust and influence.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">1.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Track behavioural shifts:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"> Behavioural changes are a great way to assess ROI in terms of brand trust and cultural influence.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">2.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Watch how people move:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"> When your company begins to influence how they talk and act, it shows a positive influence.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">3.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Measure adoption velocity:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"> the rate at which people, such as staff, move from resisting change to owning it.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">4.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Monitor repeat business:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span></span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">This is self-explanatory.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">5.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Link soft metrics to hard results: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Brand trust is not only about the number of renewals and referrals, but also about the ease of doing business with this brand. How quickly do customers forgive mistakes?</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">6.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Observe engagement signals:</span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"> Think packed stadiums and loyal fans.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">7.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Track employee and customer retention: Turnover costs companies millions. So how is yours?</span></strong></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">8.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Analyse loyalty shifts</span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">: One company measures ROI primarily through retention rather than immediate revenue.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">9.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Track brand presence at decision points: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">How does your brand show up at the point of decision? Do people ask about it, compare it or recommend it?</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">10.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Assess ownership and accountability: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Do people treat the business as their own?</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">11.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Measure goodwill-driven actions: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">How often do employees, customers or partners choose discretionary actions that help the organisation?</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">12.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Track relational trust signals: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Are customers treating you like they trust you? Is it demonstrated in their behaviour?</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">13.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Measure cross-product adoption: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">When customers add a second or third service, they are voting (and trusting you) with their wallet.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">14.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Keep an eye on social media engagement: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">User comments and engagement rates on social media platforms help you check the pulse of your business.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">15.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Look for real-world recognition: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">When people recall what your organisation has said and done, then you know you have influence.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">16.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Track unprompted conversion moments: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Unprompted conversation moments are where credibility creates outcomes without effort.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18pt; line-height: 115%;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">17.<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Analyse long-term brand performance: </span></strong><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">Look at the brand&rsquo;s historical performance over time. Look at customer loyalty, repeat engagement, word-of-mouth growth and long-term revenue. They reveal intangible factors like trust and reputation.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="line-height: 115%;"><span lang="EN-US" style="mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US;">&nbsp;</span></p>	1	65232e6a-fab0-4c2d-920d-59eb9a398865
e840e683-c5d5-45c6-8ecb-e94102d66110	2026-02-11 17:12:06.159172+02	2026-02-11 17:16:38.103578+02	post/cd139323f182425ab340c6fc9e919656.png	Connecting CSI to business	The most impactful CSI initiatives are deeply integrated with your business's values and expertise. At GoldOurs, we believe that companies with a purpose are better positioned for long-term success.	connecting-csi-to-business-1	<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">Some will find it hard to believe that corporate social investment (CSI) has been around for more than 200 years, beginning with the initiatives of industrialists Andrew Carnegie and John D Rockefeller.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">Since then, CSI has evolved, but not far from its intention to do good, not only for others but for the businesses that are advancing development investments that address the historical inequalities in South Africa, in particular.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">South Africa&rsquo;s CSI roots date to the 1950s, when Anglo American established its Chairman&rsquo;s Fund to pioneer large-scale social investment.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">It was only in the 1990s that organisations, both globally and in South Africa, became more strategic about CSI. Fortuitously, it was at the same time that the King Report on Corporate Governance, and environmental, social and governance requirements took centre stage.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">It&rsquo;s clear that CSI makes more sense when it connects to business strategy, transforming it from a "nice-to-have" charitable expense into a strategic imperative that drives long-term profitability, enhances brand reputation, and strengthens stakeholder relationships. </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">By aligning social initiatives with core business competencies&mdash;such as leveraging technology for community education or leveraging supply chains to empower local entrepreneurs&mdash;companies create shared value that benefits society and the bottom line.</span><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">But is it easier said than done?&nbsp; Here are four steps to take to connect CSI to your business:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #001d35;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/7ZNkCrC2/Steps-to-connect-CSI-to-business.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="720"></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 21.0pt; background: white;"><strong><img src="https://postimg.cc/ts7fffNq" alt=""></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #001d35; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;"><span style="color: #0a0a0a; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;">So why is it important:</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 21.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #001d35; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #001d35;">Strategic alignment (creating shared value)</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">Align CSI with the core business to ensure sustainability and relevance. It needs to make sense why your business is getting involved. For example, support small businesses in the company's supply chain to become more compliant and efficient, thereby strengthening the company's own supply chain.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 21.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #001d35; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #001d35;">Boosting brand reputation and trust</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">CSI builds loyalty, trust, and transparency among consumers, employees, and investors. </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 21.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #001d35; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #001d35;">Improving employee engagement and talent acquisition&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">A robust, purpose-driven CSI strategy increases employee pride, morale, and productivity. This is a major contributor to attracting talent and retaining staff.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 21.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #001d35; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #001d35;">Enhancing risk management and operations&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">CSI can be used to build a "social license to operate," particularly in regions with high inequality or in industries that directly impact communities. Communities help to mitigate the long-term risks, while regulatory compliance ensures these expenditures are both compliant and effective.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraph" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; background: white;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #0a0a0a;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #001d35;">Innovation and growth opportunities</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Calibri',sans-serif; mso-ascii-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-hansi-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #0a0a0a;">Connecting CSI to business can uncover new market opportunities when undeveloped communities open up to products and services. Furthermore, sustainable solutions can lead to new, eco-friendly or socially responsible products that meet growing consumer demand.</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
23b2cade-1a15-45e2-8fa9-550cc03bd995	2026-02-17 15:21:00.591205+02	2026-02-17 15:24:34.375259+02	post/f1c2dd606f5e46a690b31719751b346b.png	CSI's talent connection	Top talent want to work for a company that aligns with their personal values. A strong commitment to the community boosts employee engagement & helps you attract and retain the right workforce.	csis-talent-connection	<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Top talent, particularly among younger generations, who prioritise working for socially responsible organisations. By integrating CSI into core business functions&mdash;such as sustainability, ethics, and community support&mdash;companies create a compelling value proposition and build a positive employer brand that resonates with job seekers seeking purpose beyond a salary.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-size: 8.5pt; font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #636363; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Key connections between CSI and talent attraction</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0cm;" type="disc">\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Purpose-driven employer brand:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Companies with strong, authentic CSI commitments are viewed more favourably by potential hires. A 2016 study found 78% of millennials say CSR influences their decision to work for an organisation.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Increased engagement and retention:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Actively involving employees in CSI initiatives (e.g., volunteering) boosts pride, purpose, and loyalty, reducing staff turnover.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Active involvement:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Employee volunteer programmes are on the rise, with 75% of companies reporting their use in 2022 to connect employees with company values.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #0a0a0a; margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Enhanced recruitment marketing:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;Showcasing CSI efforts in job postings and company materials differentiates firms from competitors and attracts candidates who share similar values.</span></li>\r\n<li class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 9.0pt; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list 36.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Developing future talent pipelines:</span></strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;CSI initiatives, particularly in education and skills development, help build talent pipelines in communities, nurturing the next generation of potential employees.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Strategies for leveraging CSI to attract talent</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><strong><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/V6CVxg43/goldours-attracting-talent-with-CSI.jpg" alt="Attracting talent through CSI" width="1280" height="720"></span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Effective CSI, therefore, is not just about writing checks; it is a strategic investment in reputation and culture that makes a company a more attractive place to work.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">More reading</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">Forbes. 19 April 2023. <a title="Attracting Talent Through Corporate Social Responsibility: 3 Myths Debunked." href="https://www.forbes.com/sites/adp/2016/02/24/attracting-talent-through-corporate-social-responsibility-3-myths-debunked/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Attracting Talent Through Corporate Social Responsibility: 3 Myths Debunked.</a> Benjamin Laker.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 18.0pt; background: white;"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; color: #0a0a0a; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;">&nbsp;</span></p>	1	c727e18b-e985-403c-8243-9ad2c4a77b78
a87e86e4-96e2-4ee8-aaa4-7dea11fb316c	2026-02-28 17:08:54.633012+02	2026-02-28 17:10:53.291259+02	post/c1ec95800dd949eaa5a600c0370ce121.jpeg	Hidden cost of not thinking: Why leaders stay in crisis mode	Most leaders understand the importance of strategic thinking, but few protect time for it. The result is that strategy quietly suffers.	hidden-cost-of-not-thinking-why-leaders-stay-in-crisis-mode-1	<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Most leaders understand the importance of strategic thinking, but few protect time for it.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Across the sectors &mdash; public and private &mdash; we observe a common pattern: Intelligent, capable executives trapped in operational overload. Calendars are full. Meetings dominate the day. Emails spill into evenings. Weekends become catch-up sessions.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">The result is that strategy quietly suffers.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">The crisis cycle</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">When leaders do not intentionally create time to think:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">1. Strategy is replaced by reaction.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">2. Risk management becomes firefighting.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">3. Meetings multiply without clear outcomes.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">4. Work is duplicated.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">5. Staff operate below their true potential.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">The result is that the organisation becomes permanently busy &mdash; but not necessarily effective.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">The real issue</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">The issue is not competence. It is not commitment. It is not intelligence. It is a lack of structured thinking time embedded into organisational design. Without it, the organisation defaults to operational survival.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">The GoldOurs perspective</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">At GoldOurs, we believe sustainable growth requires:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Governance and direction</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Talent management and development</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Systems and processes</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Financial and compliance discipline.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';"><img src="https://i.postimg.cc/htXRVJZZ/essential-sustainable-growth-elements.jpg"></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Strategic thinking is the thread that connects these four essentials.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black'; mso-ansi-language: EN; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">If your leadership team is stuck in operational overload and believes you and your organisation can benefit from structured organisational design, governance strengthening, or executive coaching, contact GoldOurs at </span><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: 'Cambria',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Cambria; mso-bidi-font-family: Cambria; mso-ansi-language: EN; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;"><a href="mailto:info@goldours.co.za"><span style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">info@goldours.co.za</span></a></span><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 115%; font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black'; mso-ansi-language: EN; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;">.</span></p>	1	65232e6a-fab0-4c2d-920d-59eb9a398865
ed989aee-a181-4d39-b7d3-5f35a4a27e15	2026-03-02 10:58:27.212315+02	2026-03-02 11:00:04.791059+02	post/54581fca8ebb49a8b9ce61e8169df27b.jpeg	Busy is ineffective: When capable people operate below their role	Many senior managers are working hard. But are they working at the right level?	busy-is-ineffective-when-capable-people-operate-below-their-role	<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Many senior managers are working hard. But are they working at the right level?</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Operating below role expectation</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">When thinking time disappears, executives:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Dive into operational detail permanently</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: center 216.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Solve problems others should own<span style="mso-tab-count: 1;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: center 216.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Approve minor issues</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: 106.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Rewrite reports<span style="mso-tab-count: 1;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: 106.0pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Attend meetings that require updates, not leadership.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Over time, this creates two risks:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Senior leaders function as administrators.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Middle managers stop developing strategic capacity.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">The organisation becomes structurally dependent on over-functioning leaders.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Alone time and team thinking time</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Strategic thinking requires:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Solo reflection</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Structured leadership discussions</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Risk anticipation conversations</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Future-focused planning.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">These cannot happen in rushed operational meetings.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">If your leadership team is stuck in operational overload and would benefit from structured organisational design, governance strengthening, or executive coaching, contact GoldOurs at <a href="mailto:info@goldours.co.za">info@goldours.co.za</a>.</span></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
e8b4d7bc-4ec9-4565-b924-8094aeac744b	2026-03-03 17:20:54.87312+02	2026-03-03 17:20:54.873168+02	post/7a017b99405c46888f6cad050baa6b0e.jpeg	Role clarity, delegation, and the discipline of 80% capacity	Welcome to our ‘gold nuggets’, where we share insights from the work that GoldOurs has completed recently. In the previous article, we discussed how being busy can be ineffective for capable people	role-clarity-delegation-and-the-discipline-of-80-capacity	<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">One of the most overlooked leadership principles is this: No sustainable organisation runs at 100% capacity.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">The 80% principle</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">High-performing teams operate at approximately 80% capacity. Because the remaining 20% absorbs:</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Unexpected crises</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Staff absences</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Strategic opportunities</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Innovation</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Rest and mental reset.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">When teams operate permanently at 100%:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Anxiety increases</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Errors multiply</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Strategic thinking disappears</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Burnout accelerates</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Leadership discipline suffers.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Proper role clarification requires:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Clear job descriptions aligned to strategy</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Delegation that develops others</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Leaders stepping into detail only temporarily</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast" style="text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol;"><span style="mso-list: Ignore;">&middot;<span style="font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Active calendar management.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">Operating at 80% is not laziness. It is strategic maturity.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="tab-stops: 142.4pt;"><span lang="EN" style="font-family: 'Arial',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Aptos Black';">If your leadership team is stuck in operational overload and would benefit from structured organisational design, governance strengthening, or executive coaching, contact GoldOurs at info@goldours.co.za.</span><!-- [if !supportAnnotations]--><!--[endif]--></p>	1	767199a9-1c08-4728-bf53-6d701f6f5f66
\.


